Centos 7 MariaDB Server install!


1. sudo yum install mariadb-server -y

2. sudo systemctl start mariadb

3. sudo systemctl enable mariadb

4. sudo mysql_secure_installation

4.1. Set root password? [Y/n] y
4.2. Remove anonymous users? [Y/n] y
4.3. Disallow root login remotely? [Y/n] n (If you are going to open it for remote access, choose N, otherwise you can continue as Y.)
4.4. Remove test database and access to it? [Y/n] y
4.5. Reload privilege tables now? [Y/n] y

